entry.content: On roadside.

entry.title: Paspalum distichum
entry.content: Growing in the middle of the dried out Riddells Creek at Wybejong Park.

entry.title: Lonicera tatarica
entry.content: Came up in in-laws' garden. It was 1.5m tall when we pulled it out. Could be first record in Australia.

entry.title: Ehrharta erecta var. erecta
entry.content: 2nd pic shows flowers. This is a serious weed. Taking over areas and easily spread by Council graders on dirt roads. Seed are enjoyed by seed-eating birds including finches and crimson rosellas.

entry.title: Vellereophyton dealbatum
entry.content: New species record for Riddells Creek.

entry.title: Trifolium fragiferum var. fragiferum
entry.content: Growing alongside a dam.

entry.title: Conyza bonariensis
entry.content: One plant on the side of an old dam. 5cm tall.

entry.title: Linum trigynum
entry.content: Many thousands of plants at this site. Mostly single-stemmed and upright but occasionally multi-stemmed and ascending stems on plants one foot wide. Flowers very small, same size as Cicendia and Sebaea.

entry.title: Chrysolina quadrigemina, Hypericum perforatum subsp. veronense
entry.content: Chrysolina beetles on St John's Wort.

entry.title: Cicendia filiformis
entry.content: New species record for Riddells Creek. Common in the two main open areas at Conglomerate Gully.

entry.title: Tolpis barbata
entry.content: New species record for Conglomerate Gully.

entry.title: Linaria pelisseriana
entry.content: New species record for Riddells Creek.

entry.title: Hyacinthoides hispanica
entry.content: Anthers bluer than depicted in photo. Flowers not or sub-secund. Plants growing around the garden, mostly in the lawn.

entry.title: Myosotis discolor
entry.content: A few plants in garden lawn.

entry.title: Veronica arvensis
entry.content: Growing in garden lawn.

entry.title: Pieris rapae rapae, Rubus fruticosus spp. agg.
Lotus subbiflorus
entry.content: Very hairy. Umbel 3-flowered.

entry.title: Agonoscelis rutila, Marrubium vulgare
entry.content: Horehound Bug on Horehound!

entry.title: Mentha X piperita, Pieris rapae rapae
entry.content: Leaves petiolate and 9cm x 3cm further down the stem.

entry.title: Dodonaea viscosa 'Purpurea'
entry.content: Could be Dodonaea viscosa subsp. spatulata but, whichever the case, it is a weed at this location.

entry.title: Rubus fruticosus spp. agg., Trapezites phigalioides
Gladiolus cardinalis
entry.content: A few plants in a (weedy) bush setting. One record on FIS and none at the Herbarium. Got to be a contender for 'prettiest weed'!

entry.title: Isolepis levynsiana
entry.content: In a winter-inundated, summer-dry depression made a little deeper by tyre tracks.

entry.title: Isolepis hystrix
entry.content: Tiny plants in a clay pan - winter inundation, summer dry.

entry.title: Sonchus asper s.s., Sonchus asper subsp. glaucescens
Hakea laurina
entry.content: Just one plant.

entry.title: Conyza bonariensis
entry.content: A new, emerging weed in Riddells Creek. seems to prefer wet sites like drainage lines, road edges and other places prone to temporary inundation.

entry.title: Oxalis purpurea
entry.content: Large infestation in the cemetery.

entry.title: Ulex europaeus
entry.content: Plants at 2 sites.

entry.title: Acacia iteaphylla
entry.content: Only one plant. Obviously a garden escapee. No others have been seen escaping in Riddells Creek.

entry.title: Erigeron karvinskianus
entry.content: Appeared in a damp spot - now removed.

entry.title: Conium maculatum
entry.content: A declared noxious weed.

entry.title: Prunella vulgaris
entry.content: In a swampy area.

entry.title: Acacia pravissima
entry.content: I suspect the main plant was deliberately planted on the side of the track but there were seedlings that were obviously not planted.

entry.title: Hypochaeris radicata, Trapezites lutea lutea
entry.content: First lutea of the season although I haven't had chance to look much before this date.

entry.title: Oxalis pes-caprae
entry.content: This infestation has since been removed but the species appears from time to time around Riddells Creek.

entry.content: Location approximate.
